  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b001",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "How to Awaken",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b002",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Whenever an effect instructs you to Awaken, choose one of the available Godforms and place its card over your Titan’s illustration on the Titan Sheet. Note its name in the Godform section of the Argo Sheet and mark the associated box—this means this Godform becomes ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "unavailable",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " until the next Divine Surge (see Divine Surges on p. 23). If there are no available Godforms, you cannot Awaken. ",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b003",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Immediate Effects of Awakening",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b004",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "As soon as you Awaken, immediately:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b006",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "p. 43).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b008",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "as you are Awakened, you ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "cannot lose this token",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b010",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "tokens, as well as Despair tokens (but not Ambrosia tokens).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b013",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "tom right of your Awakening card (usually 2).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b015",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " value and perform a ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Bonus Attack",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " (see p. 56). These are not regular actions. ",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b017",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "on the various game elements always include the  symbol. That’s right. Each time you Awaken, the ripples of power are felt for many, many leagues. Your Adversary takes notice and moves towards the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Argo",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " (see Adversary Activation, p. 16).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b018",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Other Awakening Rules",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b019",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "The following rules changes apply to you as long as you are Awak-ened:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b021",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "the Power Pool",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " instead of ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "your Titan Power die.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b023",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "card.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b025",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Attacks use statistics and effects denoted on the Godform card and cannot be combined with your weapons. When you declare this Attack, the Godform card is considered to be your ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "active power",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " (instead of an active weapon).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b027",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "live: By the power of the Dead Gods…",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " card into the Obol deck. Remove it from the deck when you finish resolving the Obol Draw. In other words, only you get two ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "You live!",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " Obol cards during your Obol Draws!",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b029",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "turn, you may discard one  token to immediately stand up. ",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b030",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Ending the Awakening",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b031",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "At the start of your turn",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ", you must discard one ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Trespass",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " token from your Godform card. Note that some other Godform abilities may also use  tokens for other effects. If you cannot discard a  token at the start of your turn, ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "return the Godform card to the supply",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". You lose all bonuses provided by it. Then, if you awakened as a result of an Obol Draw, ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "you die",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". If you have awakened through any other means, after you end your Awakening, continue resolv-ing your turns as normal.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b032",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Summonings in Battle",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b033",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Summoning rules were described on p. 22. However, summoning Nymphs in Battle needs some clarification. First of all, most Sum-monings have a steep requirement that needs to be met before you are able to perform it (for example, at least one Titan needs to die). This requirement always refers to the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "current Battle",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ".Most Summonings specify the moment they can be used. If a Sum-moning does not specify this moment, it can be used like an Argo Ability (see Argo Abilities, p. 55), during the Titan Round.Otherwise, Summonings function according to the rules on p. 22.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Remember: Similarly to Awakenings, Summonings show the symbol. This means that, whenever you perform a Summoning, the Adversary immediately moves towards the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Argo",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". ",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b034",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Tests in Battle",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b035",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Many Battle abilities and effects will instruct you to perform a ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "test",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ".This is similar to tests during adventures (see Adventure Tests and Rolls p. 31).To perform a test, simply roll a single d10 and compare the result to the difficulty of the test. Some tests are associated with a spe-cific Argonaut Skill (e.g. Cunning 6+), allowing you to increase the result by your Skill value. Tests can be re-rolled using , just like Attack and Evasion Rolls (see Fate Re-rolls on p. 8).Some abilities and game effects may allow you to ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "add",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " a bonus to the test result. Unless stated otherwise, all of these effects must be declared before you perform the test. Then, after you roll the die, increase the result by the total bonus.Note that some effects will instruct you to simply roll a d10 and resolve an effect according to the result (e.g. “roll a d10. On a 10 you Awaken.”) ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Such rolls are not tests",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " (their description does not include the word “test”) and as such cannot be re-rolled us-ing .",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b036",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Ability Usage",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b037",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Titans, Mnemos cards and equipped  cards, as well as other game elements, give you access to various abilities. Some of them can be used as a free action or as a ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "reaction",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ", others will have a specific timing condition or even grant a constant effect.In general, each effect described within the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "ability box",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " on Mnemos cards, Gear cards and Titan Sheets is an ability. There are a few categories of abilities.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b038",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Active Abilities",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b039",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Abilities that require you to pay a cost are ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "active abilities",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ". The cost is always shown directly before the ability. Ability costs may in-clude:  Using a combat action,  Using a movement action, Using a complicated action,  Gaining +",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "1 Fate",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": ",  Exhausting the game element providing this ability,",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "id": "p0061.b040",
      "level": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "X",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "id": "p0061.b041",
      "children": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "  Discarding the game element providing this ability,  Discarding a charge.Other, more specific costs may be listed in the particular ability.Active ability usage is ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "always voluntary",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " (you ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "may",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " pay the cost to resolve the ability). As such, ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "these costs can never be prevented or ignored",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": " by the use of other game effects.Active abilities that have a specific timing condition (such as “dur-ing the second ability window,” “when you are about to die,” etc.) can be activated only during that specific activation time, unless ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Trespass token",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
